        <hr/>
        <article class="post-748 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized" id="post-748" role="article">
         <header class="entry-header">
          <h1 class="entry-title">
           <a href="https://bc2.berkeley.edu/2018/05/bc2-schedule-announced/" title="BC2 Schedule Announced!">
            BC2 Schedule Announced!
           </a>
          </h1>
         </header>
         <div class="entry-content">
          <p>
           The Berkeley Communications Conference (BC2) is only a few weeks away, and we have a full day of dynamic speakers, panels and networking opportunities for you! At this year’s conference, you will get a chance to hear big brand stories, learn how to apply tools and techniques to your current work, and participate in round table AMAs (Ask Me Anythings), where subject-matter experts will be available to answer your questions in a casual, knowledge-sharing setting. Check out
           <a href="http://bc2.berkeley.edu/agenda/">
            the agenda
           </a>
           ! See you June 6!
          </p>
         </div>
         <!-- .entry-content -->
        </article>
        <!-- #post-748 -->
        <hr/>
        <article class="post-740 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized" id="post-740" role="article">
         <header class="entry-header">
          <h1 class="entry-title">
           <a href="https://bc2.berkeley.edu/2018/04/bc2-2018-to-bring-in-speakers-from-pinterest-sfmoma/" title="BC2 2018 to bring in speakers from NewCo, SFMOMA">
            BC2 2018 to bring in speakers from NewCo, SFMOMA
           </a>
          </h1>
         </header>
         <div class="entry-content">
          <p>
           The
           <strong>
            7th annual Berkeley Communications Conference (BC2)
           </strong>
           on Wednesday, June 6, from 8 a.m.–5 p.m. at International House. This year’s conference brings back our full-day format and will feature various forms of storytelling around our theme: “EVOLVE.” As new communication tools and platforms surface, we must constantly find ways to adapt our message and strategy to better fit the ever-changing environment. This year communication professionals will speak on how their work has evolved and changed to reach both existing and new audiences.
          </p>
          <p>
           The morning will kick off with a continental breakfast and a welcome address from Diana Harvey, associate vice chancellor for communications and public affairs. Our day will feature two keynote speakers,
           <strong>
            Brian Monahan
           </strong>
           , Co-founder and Chief Evangelist of NewCo, and
           <strong>
            Adam Kleinberg
           </strong>
           , CEO and co-founder of advertising agency Traction. The conference will also include several breakout sessions with dynamic speakers and panelists including
           <strong>
            Nan Keeton
           </strong>
           , deputy director of external relations for the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art and
           <strong>
            Dimitri Moore
           </strong>
           , producer and filmmaker at Digital Promise.
          </p>
          <p>
           As is BC2’s tradition, the conference will shine a spotlight on our campus communicators’ creative work with the
           <a href="/contest/">
            <strong>
             BC2 Brand Awards
            </strong>
           </a>
           , and we will finish the day out with a networking happy hour!
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            The BC2 Brand Awards entry deadline is Monday, April 30, 2018.
            <a href="https://ucbevents.wufoo.com/forms/berkeley-communications-awards-2018/">
             Entry form and more details can be found here
            </a>
            . Enter today!
           </strong>
          </p>
         </div>
         <!-- .entry-content -->
        </article>
        <!-- #post-740 -->
